definition:
βραχύς, -εῖα, -ύ, 
 [in LXX chiefly for מְעַט ;] 
short; 
  (a) of time; short, little: βραχύ, Act.5:34; μετὰ β., Luk.22:58; β. τι, a short time, Heb.2:7, 9 RV, mg.; 
   (b) of distance: Act.27:28; 
   (with) of quantity or value, little, few: Jhn.6:7, Heb.2:7, 9 RV, txt.; pl., διὰ βραχέων, in few words, Heb.13:22.
† (AS)
